rComments: He was a great person and seemed super sweet and caring and really wanted you to succeed. But my god, lectures consisted of him reading a powerpoint in a super dry and monotone voice. Tried super hard to get the class to engage, just lacked the charisma to encourage it. Great guy but can be super dry. AND SO SO SO SO MUCH READING!!!!

Amazing Prof. He really cares for his students! Talk to him during office hours for further clarification or just to have a conversation. He's awesome and will help you get that A. Midterm and exam require a lot of studying but that's normal for any history course. Really interesting class all together.
Really nice professor, and very interesting. He makes going to the class worthwhile, important given the class was a 3 hour lecture 7pm-10pm. Very accommodating and helpful for papers and midterms.
